462
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:08,436
Are you having an affair?

463
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:11,434
We're in much deeper water
than that, believe me.

464
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:14,512
-lf I were you, I'd leave it alone.
-What if I don't?

465
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:17,035
Well, we could lose everything.

466
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:20,670
So before you go probing around
into my affairs...

467
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:23,237
...think long and hard.

468
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:26,397
Is it worth it to you?

469
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,632
All right, let's hear it for The Killers.

470
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:45,752
It's like four too. Her over there.
Me over here. Me over her over here.

471
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:49,356
So the four of us hanging out over
each other, but hanging out together.

472
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:52,956
I mean apart, but in the same place,
but in different places mentally.

473
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:55,634
-Something's wrong with you.
-No, that's the best part.

474
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:58,837
I'm totally fine not talking to her.
I have nothing to say to her.

475
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:01,828
Except, what I would say
if I said something to her...

476
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:06,312
...and I don't care at all if I do,
is that I'm fine not talking to her.

477
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:09,632
-Maybe I should tell her that.
-Well, you'd better hurry...

478
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:11,597
...because they're leaving.

479
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,998
I'll be right back.

480
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:23,439
Hey, you came.

481
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:26,398
Well, my friends got tickets,
and they had an extra.

482
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:29,039
Right.

483
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,632
I'll see you around.

484
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:39,831
Maybe you should tell her.

485
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:43,118
-Tell who what?
-Lindsay. That you like her.

486
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:48,674
I'm not offended. It's okay.
It's a group hang...

487
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:53,470
...and, listen, no offense here,
but I'm not really feeling the spark.

488
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:57,270
Wow. An honest conversation
with a girl.

489
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:59,078
This is new for me.

490
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:03,391
I'm gone. Thanks.

491
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:07,030
I was not talking about Cohen
the entire night.

492
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,235
It sure felt like it.

493
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:10,516
Well, what, you wanna go
somewhere else?

494
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:13,877
Maybe you should go home and log on
to some kind of Cohen chat room.

495
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:15,155
-I've had enough.
-Summer.

496
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:16,958
Hey. Where you going?

497
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:18,712
-Look, it's Seth.
-We're going home.

498
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:22,350
-Can I talk to you? Zach, I'm sorry.
-Okay, I'm gonna go jump off the pier.

499
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:23,839
Zach, wait.

500
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:27,595
I just want to tell you I don't want
to talk. I'm fine with this. You and him.

501
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:29,672
Me and her.
Zach sure is a fast walker.

502
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:31,353
Just stop trailing us, all right?

503
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:33,750
-I'm not trailing--
-Zach, will you wait, please?

504
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:36,196
-I just--
-Just beat it.

505
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:37,952
Duckie.

506
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:39,195
Please.

507
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:42,879
Please.

508
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:52,439
-lf you promise to stop calling me Duckie.
-I can't make any promises.

509
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:02,476
-Where you going? Can I give you a lift?
-I couldn't ask any more from you.

510
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:05,552
Nor thank you enough
for one of the worst evenings of my life.

511
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:08,280
I know. Seth's not ready to date yet.
It was a bad idea.

512
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:10,032
It was a colossally bad idea.

513
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:12,270
Epically bad. The invasion of lraq...

514
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:15,034
-...Iooks pretty good in comparison.
-Okay. You're right.

515
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,714
-Let me talk to you for a second.
-No, Ryan. You can't.

516
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:21,072
I've listened to enough talk
for one night, okay?

517
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:23,237
See you at school.

518
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:35,750
Come here. You'll never believe this.
Stephen's daughter has a pony too.

519
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:39,117
-She boards at the same stable as China.
-What a coincidence.

520
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:41,955
How cute is that little riding park?

521
00:31:42,120 --> 00:31:44,236
At Christmas they string lights
in the trees.

522
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:49,190
Y es. My daughter and her Shetland
spend all their Saturdays there.

523
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:53,393
Stephen, about the meeting,
I wanted to apologize--

524
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:56,836
You know, Kirsten is the one
who renovated the stable and the park.

525
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,231
Then sold it back to the original owners
at twice the cost.

526
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:03,917
Preservation and profit.
That's your motto, right, Kirsten?

527
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:07,109
Well, that's every developer's dream.

528
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:11,113
Funny. Mine's Jude Law
on a zebra-skin rug.

529
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:15,155
Your drink's looking empty.
Can I get you another?

530
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:17,908
-Only if you two join me.
-Be careful, Stephen.

531
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:20,799
Kirsten here's got
a bit of a hollow leg.

532
00:32:21,280 --> 00:32:22,998
-What are you drinking?
-Champagne.

533
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:24,229
Make it two.

534
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,678
-Done.
-Thank you.

535
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:31,079
See? I'm not totally useless.

536
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:34,471
-I never said--
-Apology accepted. I'm going to get...

537
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:38,997
...Mr. Herbert's contract from my purse.
Make sure he gets another whiskey sour.

538
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:47,072
-Hey.
-Hey.

539
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:49,310
-How was your night?
-Not good. You?

540
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:51,519
Worse.

541
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,797
You didn't like Alex?

542
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,598
And you and Lindsay?

543
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,552
Not even close.

544
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:00,678
What are you gonna do now?

545
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:06,078
-Actually, I was gonna go and....
-Go for it.

546
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:07,753
-Yeah?
-Yes.

547
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:09,194
What are you gonna do?

548
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:11,555
-I was gonna maybe--
-Good idea.

549
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:14,196
-All right. See you.
-All right. See you.

550
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:19,359
Great show.
I hope you guys come back soon.

551
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:27,315
So to recap...

552
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:31,075
...I got discoed by
two girls in one night.

553
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:34,550
And, unfortunately, that's just not
the first time that's happened.

554
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:38,508
-Actually, I'm not surprised.
-Thank you. Keep twisting the knife.

555
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:42,150
-I'm not in enough pain.
-You're hurting? Not Summer or Lindsay?

556
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:46,470
Yeah, well, at least
everybody's miserable, right?

557
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:50,030
Anyways, sorry about the whole...

558
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:53,510
...group hang or whatever that was.

559
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,114
Good night.

560
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:08,755
-Hard to believe those girls running out.
-Don't make me try and feel better.

561
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:11,514
What with you being
so bratty and immature.

562
00:34:12,160 --> 00:34:14,913
-Good. You weren't.
-And even...

563
00:34:15,240 --> 00:34:17,037
...sometimes...

564
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,272
...a little...

565
00:34:19,720 --> 00:34:21,039
...charming.

566
00:34:21,200 --> 00:34:23,475
Especially when you're not
talking about Summer.

567
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:26,509
-I know. I just--
-And knowing is half the battle...

568
00:34:26,680 --> 00:34:30,275
...so perhaps there's a little hope
for you yet.

569
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:36,472
You want to get ice cream
or something?

570
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:39,030
-lce cream as a nightcap.
-Yeah.

571
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:42,112
-You really are 8.
-And three-quarters.

572
00:34:52,720 --> 00:34:54,073
Let's go.

573
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:57,876
I'll buy, but no more than two scoops.

574
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:04,799
All right.

575
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:54,755
-Keeping watch?
-What are you doing here?

576
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:58,909
I was headed to your house.
I thought I'd surprise you.

577
00:35:59,080 --> 00:36:00,911
So this means...?

578
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:07,671
I'm not sure exactly, except...

579
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:11,873
...I guess I better prepare myself
for some drama, huh?

580
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,951
You have no idea.

581
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:33,474
Hi.

582
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:36,159
Need a lift?

583
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:41,353
No, thanks.
The bus will be here soon.

584
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:54,829
Okay. Did you not understand
the part about me taking the bus?

585
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,116
-All right. Hold on.
-Don't.

586
00:36:57,520 --> 00:37:01,069
It's my fault. I knew it was
gonna be a disaster with Seth.

587
00:37:01,240 --> 00:37:04,232
-Then why'd you say yes?
-I thought you were asking me out.

588
00:37:07,080 --> 00:37:09,958
-I didn't mean to say that out loud.
-What?

589
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:15,278
I thought that I was saying yes to you.

590
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:22,757
-Where's that stupid bus?
-You did? Because l....

591
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:26,030
I mean, you think I'm an idiot.

592
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:31,070
Yeah, well, I guess that's the twist,
because it turns out I'm the idiot.

593
00:37:33,440 --> 00:37:36,000
No, no, you're not. I....

594
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:42,437
When I asked you out that day
for Seth l....

595
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,233
Well, l....

596
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:47,392
Keep talking, Ryan.

597
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:50,239
I wanted it to be me.

598
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:54,513
I did. I just didn't think
in a million years you'd say yes.

599
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:01,988
Then I've been right all along.

600
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,359
You are an idiot.

601
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:09,679
An idiot you'd go out with sometime?

602
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:12,719
It's possible.

603
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:23,314
-Party's over.
-Finally.

604
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:26,870
I literally had to push Stephen Herbert
out the door.

605
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:28,998
Deal's back on?

606
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:32,994
He re-signed his contracts. Hopefully,
he'll remember that in the morning.

607
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:34,912
Julie Cooper.

608
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:37,589
Definitely understands
the weakness of man.

609
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:39,239
You were gone for a while.

610
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,675
Well, I was driving around.

611
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:45,193
Thinking how I find myself again...

612
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:47,517
...in a very familiar triangle.

613
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:50,990
-What triangle is that?
-You. Me.

614
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:52,838
Your dad.

615
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:56,318
-He's guilty, isn't he?
-He's guilty of something.

616
00:38:56,960 --> 00:39:00,191
-Something he thinks we shouldn't know.
-Well, you've never been one...

617
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:02,920
-...to shy away from the truth.
-I can start now.

618
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:07,639
A man can make a nice life
out of Cheetos and Dr. Phil.

619
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,916
Not the man I love.

